Sure, here are some example sentences in Serbian that use the word "odnosi" in different forms and positions, with the word highlighted with a star (*) and translations in English in parenthesis:

1. *Odnosi* između Srbije i Kosova su napeti. (*Relations* between Serbia and Kosovo are tense.)
2. Njihovi *odnosi* su se pogoršali posle svađe. (Their *relationship* worsened after the argument.)
3. Predstavnici dveju kompanija razgovaraju o *odnosima* buduće saradnje. (Representatives of the two companies are discussing *terms* of future collaboration.)
4. *Odnos* cena i kvaliteta je veoma bitan za kupce. (The *ratio* of price and quality is very important for customers.)
5. On je stručnjak za *odnose* sa javnošću. (He is an expert in *public relations*.)